comments.body:
@dgoodwin 

It doesn't do a 3-way merge. It merges an existing object with the requested params, then compares the merged object to the latest object. If there are differences, it makes makes a request to the API (patch, update, post, etc.), and returns 'changed', along with the new object. If no differences, then  no request is sent to the API, and OK is returned, along with the current object.

The modules call the API, rather than relying directly on `oc` or `kubectl`. So when the 3-way logic does land on the server, we'll want to switch to letting the API handle merging and comparing objects.
